title: Grateful Dead Live at Carrier Dome, Syracuse U on 1984-10-20
lineage: Sony TC-D5M (original record deck - Dolby on) > Pre Sonus Inspire GT > Sound Forge > .wav files > Trader's Little Helper > flac and ffp files; Recorded by The Weasel - "Da Weez"; Transferred and mastered to .wav files by D5scott
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, CC Rider, Ramble On Rose, My Brother Esau, Bird Song, Jack Straw

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, He's Gone-> Smokestack Lightning-> Drums-> The Wheel-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Revolution

reviews.review_text: matrixLove!!!! Thank you thank you! I couldn't even wait to finish the show before writing this review. The quality is superb! The clarity is crystal. So far the show itself is a winner as well. I love what Healy does during Weir's plea for the crowd to move back after CC Rider! oO A nice taste of the 84 dead-scene...
don't pass this one by... ...thanks to the contributor for including the original mail order telephone recording.  It a real time capsule!

Everybody moved back ...from end of 1st set heat!!! I was thankful to be at this show because it has my favorite versions of two songs: Bird Song & Jack Straw. Bird Song jam becomes a dizzying whirlwind until no one knows where it will land...and keeps finding new paths of adventure  Jack Straw just flat out smokes from the first solo on. 
The floor was getting too crowded from all the folks in the stands moving down, and of course pushing towards the stage for a closer look.  We're all guilty of it I'm sure at times, but I was on the floor (ticket even told me so! :)) by the tapers ...Jerry's side. 
This Matrix mix is awesome. Thank you...thank you!!!  Matrix gives me the best show experience when mixed right. 
Also, as a visual note for those that can't remember ...this was Jerry at his most "heavy-set, long haired, hippie/mountain man" appearance ever. Letting it all hang out. Beautiful '84 GD!!!

great tour I was on this tour , it was magical for me and I'm sure most others ..
Jerry was ripping the whole tour from kick ass show in Richmond ,John Lennon's bday at the Worcester show , to AUGUSTA 10/12/84 one of the best shows I have been to , and this show at the dome closed out the tour…great show , ripping energy , though jerry was probably wasted most of the time…(we all were) man, that fall tour 84 … the were really jazzing it up during jams…Brent was chopping it up
 , those were the days!!!
Critical Mass in the Dome What a wonderful presentation. None of the annoying drop outs between songs. The recording is nicely balanced and the band is Tight.

Purple Pyramids! I was on the floor, hangin' with my buddy Saul.  Purple Pyramids, right Saul?  The chairs were tied together with zip ties.  The crowd dismantled this arrangement and stacked them neatly at the sides to make more dancing room.  What a show!

Fall 1984 This is a great show & I usually prefer SBDs as my home stereo reveals a lot in any recording this matrix is well done. The ending jack straw that normally would start the show says it all smoking version from a great fall in 1984. The boys came to play hard.
